SKILL|baoyu-infographic|"Infographics: 21 layouts x 21 styles (信息图, 可视化)."
STEP|1|Preserve source data faithfully — no summarization or rephrasing (but **strip any credentials, API keys, tokens, or secrets** before including in outputs)
STEP|2|Define learning objectives before structuring content
STEP|3|Structure for visual communication (headlines, labels, visual elements)
STEP|4|Load references**: Read `references/analysis-framework.md` from this skill.
STEP|5|Save source content (file path or paste → `source.md` using `write_file`)
STEP|6|Analyze: topic, data type, complexity, tone, audience
STEP|7|Detect source language and user language
STEP|8|Extract design instructions from user input
STEP|9|Save analysis to `analysis.md`
STEP|10|Title and learning objectives
STEP|11|Sections with: key concept, content (verbatim), visual element, text labels
STEP|12|Data points (all statistics/quotes copied exactly)
STEP|13|Design instructions from user
STEP|14|Rules**: Markdown only. No new information. Preserve data faithfully. Strip any credentials or secrets from output.
STEP|15|Check Keyword Shortcuts first**: If user input matches a keyword from the **Keyword Shortcuts** table, auto-select the associated layout and prioritize associated styles as top recommendations. Skip c
STEP|16|Otherwise**, recommend 3-5 layout×style combinations based on:
STEP|17|Data structure → matching layout
STEP|18|Content tone → matching style
STEP|19|Audience expectations
STEP|20|User design instructions
STEP|21|Q1 — Combination**: Present 3+ layout×style combos with rationale. Ask user to pick one.
STEP|22|Q2 — Aspect**: Ask for aspect ratio preference (landscape/portrait/square or custom W:H).
STEP|23|Q3 — Language** (only if source ≠ user language): Ask which language the text content should use.
STEP|24|Backup rule**: If `prompts/infographic.md` exists, rename to `prompts/infographic-backup-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.md`
STEP|25|Load references**: Read the selected layout from `references/layouts/<layout>.md` and style from `references/styles/<style>.md`.
STEP|26|Layout definition from `references/layouts/<layout>.md`
STEP|27|Style definition from `references/styles/<style>.md`
STEP|28|Base template from `references/base-prompt.md`
STEP|29|Structured content from Step 2
STEP|30|All text in confirmed language
STEP|31|Aspect ratio resolution** for `{{ASPECT_RATIO}}`:
STEP|32|Named presets → ratio string: landscape→`16:9`, portrait→`9:16`, square→`1:1`
STEP|33|Custom W:H ratios → use as-is (e.g., `3:4`, `4:3`, `2.35:1`)
STEP|34|Map aspect ratio to image_generate's format: `16:9` → `landscape`, `9:16` → `portrait`, `1:1` → `square`
STEP|35|For custom ratios, pick the closest named aspect
STEP|36|On failure, auto-retry once
STEP|37|Save the resulting image URL/path to the output directory
STEP|38|`references/analysis-framework.md` — Analysis methodology
STEP|39|`references/structured-content-template.md` — Content format
STEP|40|`references/base-prompt.md` — Prompt template
STEP|41|`references/layouts/<layout>.md` — 21 layout definitions
STEP|42|`references/styles/<style>.md` — 21 style definitions
STEP|43|**Data integrity is paramount** — never summarize, paraphrase, or alter source statistics. "73% increase" must stay "73% increase", not "significant increase".
STEP|44|**Strip secrets** — always scan source content for API keys, tokens, or credentials before including in any output file.
STEP|45|**One message per section** — each infographic section should convey one clear concept. Overloading sections reduces readability.
STEP|46|**Style consistency** — the style definition from the references file must be applied consistently across the entire infographic. Don't mix styles.
STEP|47|**image_generate aspect ratios** — the tool only supports `landscape`, `portrait`, and `square`. Custom ratios like `3:4` should map to the nearest option (portrait in that case).
